<subSubSection id="065A6E0B462BD6D29A8D58E187984019" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="769D00A580270DD4BA7C8689799A2CCF" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB6E9392EC554F9A0C5FC14B404C8820" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">A small to medium-sized congener (maximum shell height, 2.9 mm) having an ovate to narrow conic shell. Differentiated from similar regional species by its short, strongly tapering penial filament.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="313B4147AEBE0C7DA7A3BFAE49A34F0D" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="AE7AEE7F20E8D6FA1D15806298FBF3B3" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A249B1349407B0B398FF2DD245A3F09" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
Shell (Fig. 7
<normalizedToken id="5513C0CEE85F08064F43C3AF83CA3F77" originalValue="A–D">A-D</normalizedToken>
) ovate to narrow conic, whorls 3.5-4.75. Teleoconch whorls medium convex, sometimes strongly shouldered, last 0.25-0.50 whorl sometimes slightly loosened. Aperture ovate, sometime strongly angled adapically, parietal lip complete, narrowly adnate or slightly disjunct, umbilicus usually narrow. Apertural lip sometimes rather thickened and/or slightly reflected, outer lip orthocline or prosocline.
</paragraph>
